<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MTA90">
<l>varattāl valiniṉaintu mātavaniṉ pātañ</l>
<l>cirattāl vaṇaṅkāṉā meṉṟē – yurattiṉā</l>
<l>līrariyāy nērvaliyō ṉāya viraṇiyaṉai</l>
<l>yōrariyāy nīyiṭanta tūṉ</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O Mātavaṉ, saying to yourself that it is thinking of [his] strength</l>
<l>because of the boon that he did not bow with [his] head before your feet,</l> 
<l>as a unique lion, you dug into the flesh of Hiraṇya<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For further examples of this particular type of cleft construction see Po. 36.1, Pū. 95.1f., 99.4, Pē. 98.4.</note> who was not to be seized</l> 
<l>directly, as an enemy dragged by [your] strength.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
